The Religious Laws are given the same weight as Civil Laws, and are under the Jurisdiction of the Temple. The Civil Laws are under the Jurisdiction of the Militia and the Trade Council. 

Residents are not required to follow the Spider Queen. They are free to follow their own gods, but they must respect the Spider Queen and her servants, the Yathrin, and the Ilythiiri Pantheon.

All must abide by both the Civil and Religious Laws, as outlined on the pillars to the left and the right.

| Civil Laws |

The Civil Laws, much like the Religious Laws, are to maintain stability and peace in Nec'perya.

 No Slavery
Slavery is not permitted in Nec'perya. Slaves brought in by outsiders will be immediately freed and the slave's owner fined. The amount of the fine will be based on the freed slave's value as an artisan, and will be remitted to the freed slave to cover the cost of their initial housing and food while they find employment.

 Treason against the Establishment
Examples: Undermining the security of Nec'perya
Punishment: Exile.

 Murder
Punishment: Physical beatings, in some cases death.

 Assault Without Cause
Punishment: Physical beatings, Restitution.

 Theft
Punishment: Restitution and/or physical punishment.
Further Details: Restitution will be a fine equal to double the value of the stolen item(s).

 Trespassing on Private Property
Punishment: See below.
Further Details: Residents of the property being trespassed upon are free to dispose of intruders as they see fit without incurring punishment, but only while on said property. If the intruder escapes the property then a civil judgement must be sought.

| Religious Laws |

All charges require the testimony of a "Credible Witness," this being someone of good standing in the City and who is not part of the offended House or offended Priestess's House.

 Sacrilege & Defilement of Sacred Sites
Examples: Despoilment of the Temple, defacement of Holy Icons.
Punishment: Exile.

 Treason against the Dread Queen
Examples: Conspiring with enemies of the Dread Queen.
Punishment: Re-education, Exile.

 Harming Spiders
Examples: Stepping on a spider, stabbing a spider
Punishment: First offense is Re-education, second offense is Death.
Further Details: Summoners are held responsible for the actions of what they bind. Therefore, any person who summons a creature or being will be responsible for any Laws it breaks, and will face the brunt of punishment. Summoned spiders are not to be harmed; however, the summoner is also held responsible for the wellbeing of their summoned spider.

 Harming a Priestess
Examples: Assaulting a Priestess, killing a Priestess.
Punishment: Re-education, Death, Exile.

 Insolence towards a Priestess
Examples: Insulting behaviour.
Punishment: Physical punishment, re-education; Exile if the offender flees punishment .
Further Details: Exemptions are made to the 'Refusal to obey' when following a higher order or mandate by the Guard, Temple or House. In these instances, no punishments will apply for the male disobeying a personal order of a priestess.  If the priestess in question chooses to push this and punishes him anyway, the Temple will decide a fitting punishment for the Priestess. 

 Male Harming a Female
Examples: Assaulting a Female, killing a female.
Punishment: Physical punishment, re-education.
Further Details: Exemptions are made in the case of self-defense, except in the case where the male was being punished for an offense.

 Consorting with the Dread Queen's Enemies
Examples: Socialising with Eilistraeean whores, dealing with those banished and disgraced.
Punishment: Physical punishment, re-education; on the third offense the punishment will match that of Treason against the Dread Queen
Further Details: Continued consorting with these enemies can be later be construed as Treason against the Dread Queen.

 Male Insolence towards Females
Examples: Insulting behaviour.
Punishment: Physical punishment; on the third offense the punishment will match that of a Male Harming a Priestess.

Value.value: The former Thran'daariv Laws pillar lies in ruins here, now.
Where once this leynode had no physical barriers surrounding it, it is now enclosed inside an adamantine fence, with each section affixed to elaborately carved, heavy marble pillars.

Value.value: The city of Nec'perya is currently undergoing reconstruction projects all across the island. Old buildings are being restored, while a few new ones seem to be popping up along the southern shore. Citizens, former slaves previously lacking in purpose or direction, busy themselves in helping out with the construction projects.
